place.name: BARNETBY LE WOLD
place.gazetteerText: BARNETBY-LE-WOLD, a parish in Glanford-Brigg district, Lincoln; on the Manchester and Lincolnshire railway, 3¾ miles NE of Brigg. It has a station, of the name of Barnetby, on the railway, and a post office, of the same name, under Ulceby. Acres, 1,630. Real property, £4,334. Pop., 828. Houses, 186. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £400.* Patron, the Bishop of Lincoln. The church is early English. There are three dissenting chapels. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
